<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="421" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,722,1937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,722,748]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tong &amp; Chen &amp; Zhang &amp; Chen &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2020" box="[899,995,722,748]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Plotinini">Plotinini</taxonomicName>
by the extraordinary pattern on the elytra (
<figureCitation box="[195,261,758,784]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Figs 1</figureCitation>
a–c). The structures of the male genitalia are similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Tong &amp; Chen &amp; Zhang &amp; Chen &amp; Wang, 2020" authorityName="Tong &amp; Chen &amp; Zhang &amp; Chen &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2020" box="[875,1063,758,784]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Sphaeroplotina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varimarginata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[875,1063,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">S. varimarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1069,1157,759,785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but can be distinguished from the later by having penis guide which is slightly longer than parameres, and stout in ventral view with widest part about 1.52× of its basal width.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="421" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,722,1937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,866,892]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Description.</emphasis>
TL: 
<quantity box="[402,568,866,893]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.94" metricValueMax="4.13" metricValueMin="3.75" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" unit="mm" value="3.94" valueMax="4.13" valueMin="3.75">3.75–4.13 mm</quantity>
, TW: 
<quantity box="[639,805,866,893]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.445" metricValueMax="3.59" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" unit="mm" value="3.445" valueMax="3.59" valueMin="3.3">3.30–3.59 mm</quantity>
, TH: 
<quantity box="[870,1036,866,893]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.015" metricValueMax="2.06" metricValueMin="1.97" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" unit="mm" value="2.015" valueMax="2.06" valueMin="1.97">1.97–2.06 mm</quantity>
, TL/TW: 1.12–1.19, PL/PW: 0.25– 0.33, EL/EW: 0.94–1.02.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,722,1937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">
Body moderately large, broadly oval, moderately convex, shining and glabrous (
<figureCitation box="[1141,1212,938,965]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Figs 1</figureCitation>
a–d). Head reddish brown with maxillary palpi and labrum yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[810,878,974,1001]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Figs 1</figureCitation>
c–d). Pronotum reddish brown, with a transverse black spot at base, scutellar shield black (
<figureCitation box="[613,679,1010,1036]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Figs 1</figureCitation>
a–c). Ground color of elytron reddish brown, with two large yellow spots at base and apex; each elytron with six dark spots as show in 
<figureCitation box="[915,1023,1046,1072]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Figure 1a</figureCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[1039,1119,1046,1072]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
). Ventral surfaces yellow to black; discrimen of metaventrite, area around coxae and external border of epipeura dark (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1244,1082,1109]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
). Legs yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[238,346,1118,1145]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Figs 1d, 1</figureCitation>
l–m).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,722,1937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">
Head moderately small, 0.38× of elytral width (EW/HW=2.62); frontal surface of head capsule slightly convex; punctures on frons fine, with long setae in punctures; eyes small, broadly oval, widest interocular distance 0.57× width of head (
<figureCitation box="[319,399,1226,1252]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
). Pronotum 0.61× as wide as elytra (EW/PW=1.65), pronotal punctures fine, similar to those on head. Punctures on elytra moderately large, irregular, and obviously larger than those on pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1305,1385,1262,1288]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,722,1937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">
Surface of prosternum slightly shagreened, punctures moderately large, with sparse short setae. Mesoventrite slightly shagreened, punctures fine, with several short setae. Metaventrite broad, punctures fine but distinctly larger near discrimen, with short sparse setae (
<figureCitation box="[612,690,1370,1397]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig 1d</figureCitation>
). Abdominal postcoxal lines complete, almost touching posterior margin of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[389,471,1406,1433]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1403,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969, habitus: a dorsal view, b lateral view, c frontal view, d ventral view, e prothorax, ventral view, f antenna, g mandible, left, dorsal view, h mandible, right, dorsal view, i maxilla, j labium, k abdomen, male l middle leg m hind leg. Scale bars: a–d: 0.5 mm; e–m: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413226/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig. 1k</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,722,1937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">
Male genitalia: Penis long and slender, penis capsule with short outer process and long inner one, apex of penis pointed (
<figureCitation box="[249,319,1478,1505]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,908,932]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,192,882]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1436,181,884]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969 a–d male genitalia: a penis, b apex of penis, c tegmen, lateral view, d tegmen, ventral view, e–f female genitalia: e spermatheca, f ovipositor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413228" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413228/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Figs 2</figureCitation>
a–b). Penis guide in lateral view short and stout, widest at base, tapering to apex, apex pointed; parameres arcuate, slightly longer than penis guide, sparsely setose on apical and inner surfaces, and with a tuft of long setae at their bases (
<figureCitation box="[374,456,1550,1576]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,908,932]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,192,882]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1436,181,884]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969 a–d male genitalia: a penis, b apex of penis, c tegmen, lateral view, d tegmen, ventral view, e–f female genitalia: e spermatheca, f ovipositor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413228" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413228/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
); penis guide in ventral view stout, widest at basal 2/5, distinctly narrowed at base, with widest part about 1.52× of basal width, apically rounded with a small protuberance (
<figureCitation box="[1095,1179,1586,1613]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,908,932]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,192,882]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1436,181,884]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969 a–d male genitalia: a penis, b apex of penis, c tegmen, lateral view, d tegmen, ventral view, e–f female genitalia: e spermatheca, f ovipositor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413228" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413228/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,722,1937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">
Female genitalia: Coxites elongate, triangular; styli distinct with terminal setae (
<figureCitation box="[1118,1193,1622,1649]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,908,932]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,192,882]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1436,181,884]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969 a–d male genitalia: a penis, b apex of penis, c tegmen, lateral view, d tegmen, ventral view, e–f female genitalia: e spermatheca, f ovipositor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413228" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413228/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig 2f</figureCitation>
); spermatheca with a subrounded nodulus and a slender cornu (
<figureCitation box="[618,700,1658,1684]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,908,932]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,192,882]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1436,181,884]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969 a–d male genitalia: a penis, b apex of penis, c tegmen, lateral view, d tegmen, ventral view, e–f female genitalia: e spermatheca, f ovipositor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413228" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413228/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig. 2e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
