<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="421" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,722,1937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1802,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoang, 1982" authorityName="Hoang" authorityYear="1982" box="[609,1045,1802,1828]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Paraplotina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamdaoensis">
<emphasis box="[609,892,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Paraplotina tamdaoensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hoang, D. N." box="[899,1045,1802,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" refId="ref3993" refString="Hoang, D. N. (1982) Ladybeetles of Viet Nam (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae). Part 1. Nha xuat ban khoa hoc va kythuat, Hanoi, 211 pp. [in Vietnamese with English summary]" type="book" year="1982">
Hoàng, 
<quantity box="[989,1045,1802,1828]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.03428" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" unit="in" value="1982.0">1982</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in structures of the male genitalia, but can be distinguished from the later by the small protuberance at the apex of penis guide in ventral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,908,932]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,192,882]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1436,181,884]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sphaeroplotina hainanensis Miyatake, 1969 a–d male genitalia: a penis, b apex of penis, c tegmen, lateral view, d tegmen, ventral view, e–f female genitalia: e spermatheca, f ovipositor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413228" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413228/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">Fig 2d</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoang" authorityYear="1982" box="[235,404,1874,1900]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Paraplotina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamdaoensis">
<emphasis box="[235,404,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">P. tamdaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, penis guide in ventral view apically rounded without protuberance (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoang, D. N." box="[1187,1331,1874,1900]" pageId="2" pageNumber="421" refId="ref3993" refString="Hoang, D. N. (1982) Ladybeetles of Viet Nam (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae). Part 1. Nha xuat ban khoa hoc va kythuat, Hanoi, 211 pp. [in Vietnamese with English summary]" type="book" year="1982">Hoàng 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, X. M. &amp; Ge, F. &amp; Ren, S. X." pageId="2" pageNumber="421" pagination="416 - 422" refId="ref4725" refString="Wang, X. M., Ge, F. &amp; Ren, S. X. (2012) The genus Paraplotina Miyatake 1969 (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) from China. The Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 88 (4), 416 - 422. https: // doi. org / 10.3956 / 2011 - 42.1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Wang 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="421">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
